e Second Class year  Required Courses  EE 325   Electromagnetic Fields EE 355   Electronics I EE 356   Electronics II EE 413    Microelectronics EE 426    Semiconductor Devices PY 308    Introduction to Nanotechnology Summer Internship Program  VMEC  Virginia Microelectronics Consortium  Undergraduate Scholars Exchange Program  10 13 week summer program between the junior and senior years Participants receive a  650 week stipend and 3 credits toward their degree at VMI Contact Colonel Addington for more information  Summer Internship Participants Declaration of Concentration Form Col  Shawn Addington Home Courses Undergrad Research Activities Grants   Publications Microelectronics Concentration VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Virginia Military Institute   Microelectronics Concentration       Virginia Military Institute   Microelectronics Concentration                     skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences L